##What Ai Technologies are emerging from the epidemic?

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

The war and epidemic plan for Innovative Economy, a special column launched by Finance and Economics during the new type of pneumonia epidemic, focuses on the new difficulties encountered by enterprises of Innovative Economy and discusses the new countermeasures that should be adopted, hope to help small and medium-sized enterprises together to overcome challenges and seize opportunities.

By suki

Editor | Wei Jia

The 2020 outbreak is often compared to SARS in 2003. Compared with 17 years ago, in this difficult epidemic battle, in addition to the day and night to fight the medical staff, increasingly mature AI technology has become a "war epidemic" force, play an important role.

Ai Is often associated with words like "loss" , "no landing" and "bubble" , but in the midst of an epidemic, AI becomes relevant to our lives.

In airports and subway stations, you've had your temperature measured by an infrared thermal imaging system; you've probably received a phone call from an intelligent robot on your way back to your apartment; when you enter an office building, an AI can tell if you're wearing a mask; in a hospital, doctors use an AI diagnostic system to quickly determine whether a patient is at risk for new pneumonia. Robots shuttle around the isolation ward, delivering food and medicine..

The epidemic has accelerated the integration of AI into urban life, both as a way to improve efficiency and as a way to reduce the risk of infection by replacing humans in some scenarios. So, in what scenarios are new opportunities opening up? Will the epidemic eventually pass, and will the need for Ai Continue in all areas?

Ai-assisted diagnosis, 2-3 seconds to find the lesion

SCENE: Hospital

The outbreak, the most tense place to be all over the hospital, especially in the Wuhan Area Hospital.

Dr Li worked at Wuhan's Central Hospital, just a stop away from the south China Seafood Market and at the heart of the outbreak. After the hospital was designated as a hospital for patients with fever, during peak hours, the hospital had an average of more than 1,000 CT scans a day, and front line radiologists had to read overnight. A chest CT has more than 300 cross-section of the film, relying on the naked eye to read a piece of film, a considerable workload.

In 2018, Wuhan Central Hospital began using Shukun's CT artificial intelligence diagnostic products, mainly in the field of coronary heart disease. Therefore, after the outbreak, Shukun Technology immediately organized R & D personnel to develop a new coronary pneumonia AI auxiliary diagnostic product during the Spring Festival, and launched in early February in Wuhan Central Hospital.

The product can pick out lesions from more than 300-slice CT images in 2-3 seconds, generate a 3-d model of the lung lobe, mark the area where the lesions are located, and then guide doctors to make reasonable patient triage to improve the detection efficiency of new coronary pneumonia.

If the patient again CT, the product can also automatically compare the patient before and after the focus changes, so that doctors can judge the condition. Wang Xiang, director of the Imaging Department at Wuhan General Hospital, has said publicly that the AI system could improve the efficiency of doctors by 50% .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Central Hospital Doctors Use Sukun neochampion pneumonia AI product

The efficiency has been improved, how to guarantee the accuracy? Shukun Science and technology related person in charge told Caijing, not only can you not make a wrong judgment, but you must also suppress false Yang, that is, because of factors such as the environment, the operation, the experimental method or the patients themselves, people who do not have positive symptoms are tested positive, these two dimensions are the difficulties of existing products.

"To control these two dimensions well, we need to make constant adjustments to the algorithms of AI system based on years of medical clinical experience and case judgment, " the official said, adding that doctors' experience and data accumulation, is the key to many AI assisted diagnostic systems going much further. It is also due to the accumulation of data in the field of coronary heart disease, this can be a rapid iteration of new pneumonia-related diagnostic AIDS.

According to reports, the AI system has been in the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital, Wuhan City Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine and dozens of hospitals across the country, and donated to the Raytheon Mountain Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Beijing Friendship Hospital Image Department uses Shukun new pneumonia AI products

In the epidemic, according to the map technology, Shang Tang technology also based on the existing intelligent diagnosis and treatment platform, for the new pneumonia was upgraded.

"One of the things that struck me about this outbreak is that good medical resources are really limited for ordinary people. The epidemic situation has accelerated to prove the effectiveness of Ai to help doctors, and more primary care institutions may choose AI products next, so that AI products with the diagnostic ability of large hospitals can be quickly replicated to the grassroots,"the person in charge told Caijing.

He believes that the AI auxiliary diagnostic system for this pneumonia, in addition to diagnosis and scientific significance. In the next stage, we should do some clinical research on the disease, and build a better prevention and control system. In the future, the application of AI technology in the field of auxiliary diagnosis will become a trend.

Non-contact thermometers can be taken without taking off the mask

SCENE: station, building

During the rework tide, stations, airports, office buildings and other public places gathering, how to monitor abnormal body temperature, has become a big problem.

Usually everyone in and out of the community, there will be one by one with the forehead temperature gun to measure, but in a crowded place, such a practice is not realistic, so AI enterprises began to show their magic power, with infrared thermometer instead.

Infrared thermometer through infrared thermal imaging camera, more than 3 meters of the crowd for non-contact remote temperature measurement, can simultaneously measure 100 people. If someone in the crowd is more than 37.3 °c, the thermometer can quickly identify and prompt the staff for a second measurement review.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Open-view "MINGJI" temperature measurement solution system

How do you mark the temperature of each person in the temperature group?

Kuang Shi Vice President Xie Yinan told financial, Kuang Shi in Ai Recognition has been done is human detection, this time they will ordinary optical camera and infrared temperature sensor camera integrated into one, after the transformation of hardware can solve this problem.

In addition, with very little skin exposed and face masks worn in winter, finding an effective place to measure body temperature is another challenge. The method adopted is to scan the mask out, then quickly through the mask to locate the position of the forehead.

"everyone is rushing to introduce infrared thermometers and there is a huge demand for them, so the speed of response is a problem. In addition, the accuracy of temperature measurement will be affected by many factors, especially in the station such a large flow of people, indoor and outdoor temperature difference, the environment is more complex places, there will inevitably be temperature fluctuations.

Infrared temperature measurement in order to ensure the accuracy of temperature measurement, a key piece of hardware called blackbody, is currently in short supply. "It used to be a small-scale product and there was not that much demand. The sudden outbreak of the epidemic, blackbody manufacturers to respond to the speed of a very high demand. Facing this unfamiliar supply chain, how to realize mass production quickly has also become a top priority for AI companies,"Wang said.

To this end, Kuang Shi introduced a new algorithm, even without black body can ensure that the human body temperature measurement error of 0.3 °C, for the industry to provide new possibilities.

There is a special case, the epidemic is currently everyone wearing masks and hats, for the staff back to work, wearing masks can easily brush face punch card and temperature, become new just.

The SenseThunder-E pyrometer + SensePass Pro SensePass is designed to automatically intercept people with abnormal body temperature and those who don't wear masks.

A number of start-ups also saw an opportunity to enter the field. The teak cluster information technology epidemic prevention and control body temperature forecast system has produced an integrated system of "face recognition + Body temperature monitoring + cloud analysis" for the relevant departments of the Shangrao government.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Forecasting system of body temperature for prevention and control of POMELO population information technology epidemic situation

"there is a need to increase the function of epidemic prevention in all walks of life. For example, schools will add gates with a temperature measuring plate and have them in place before the start of the school year, " Wang told the Financial Times, some of the manufacturing capacity, production capacity, sales channels of the company, began to take the initiative to find AI enterprises, add new function points such as temperature measurement, which is good for the industry.

New needs mean new opportunities. "This outbreak tells the AI industry that you need to take a moment to practice your inner work, such as whether your Ai Algorithm can connect to existing iot devices, such as cameras, on-off sensors, gateways, Gates, etc. , or make other morphological changes. Product First, which I think is the first thing that AI enterprises should learn during this epidemic,"Xie said.

The AI tracks the movements of a confirmed patient

SCENE: community

"Hello, this is xx community sub-district office. Are you xxx resident? Do you or your family members have cough, chest tightness and other symptoms? Do you or your family members have normal body temperature? "

You've probably been getting a lot of these AI inquires lately, as well as the fact that you have to fill in your personal information on the system every day when you go in and out of your neighborhood or office building.

It is understood that Baidu, Iflytek, Alibaba Cloud and other technology companies, "intelligent extravehicular platform" , Jingdong suke intelligent extravehicular robots have been applied in the fight against the epidemic process.

In addition, Jd.com also launched the outbreak inquiry robot, can be suspected patients to ask questions, analysis of each other whether the need for isolation treatment. Users scan the code to log in, but also to query fever clinics and designated hospitals information, can be in the "online pharmacy" to choose and buy drugs.

"But after this outbreak, I have also found that there is still room for improvement. For example, the development of the first version of the epidemic robot took only three days, and there will be a large number of users asking questions every day. Some of the questions will go beyond the original database, which will inspire us to continuously iterate the products and improve the knowledge base,"said Bo Liefeng, chief scientist at jd.com.

He added, "In addition, when we deploy the EXTRAROBOT, we actually need the human involvement of the community staff, and the team needs to build a more complete, self-iterating knowledge base to increase the level of automation. "

After the outbreak is over, the outward bound robot can also play a greater role in a variety of more densely populated scenarios, such as when logistics personnel arrive, can use the outward bound robot to confirm that goods have been delivered.

In an epidemic, it is an urgent problem how to quickly restore the movement track of a confirmed patient.

Jd.com provides a situation analysis and early warning system for high-risk populations to help the government analyze residents'movements and make early warning and screening for high-risk populations. The system can analyze the behavioral trajectories of a confirmed patient and help isolate potential close contacts.

"governments all over the country want to know where people are coming back from the epidemic areas, how to screen them efficiently, it's almost impossible to do this one by one by manpower, the spatiotemporal data is always changing dynamically, and it's related to getting through the data of the telecom operators, the government data and the corporate data. We have provided this system to 18 provinces and cities, and Beijing has found 500 close contacts,"said Jung Woo, jd.com vice president, jd.com chief data scientist for digital technology and president of jd.com, the trajectory of a diagnosed patient is the most urgent and difficult requirement, and the system often does the calculations twice a day.

Ordinary citizens can report their health status and travel records through the community epidemic intelligent management platform, and with the generated two-dimensional code access to the community.

"We have community control platforms in Yulin and Yizhuang, which are now used by more than 40,000 households every day, saving more than 40,000 sheets of paper and 40,000 minutes of form-filling time, " Jung Woo said.

Drones and agvs will be used in more ways than one

SCENE: Farm, warehouse

Since the outbreak, "nobody + " has become a high-frequency keyword.

During the Spring Festival, a video of a village official shouting words was widely circulated among friends, but what many people didn't know was that there was a drone version of the speaker.

Dji said, Dji "Yu" Mavic2 industry double-plate machine, you can choose with shouting, thermal imager and other functions, set shouting, thermal imaging temperature, aerial work spray disinfection water and other functions in one.

On February 4, Xinjiang Agriculture launched the "Xinjiang Army War epidemic" and set up a 10 million war epidemic fund to support the eradication of the epidemic. Up to now, Xinjiang Agricultural Plant Protection UAV has killed more than 400 million square meters in thousands of villages. It should be noted, however, that this type of product requires a professional to handle it.

In addition to spraying, killing and epidemic prevention, Dji also provides unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) solutions for patrol, epidemic prevention, propaganda and material delivery, Dji said.

Equipped with thermal imaging sensors, the "O" Mavic 2 industry dual-optical version

In addition to uavs, medical supplies in and out of storage and distribution, protective equipment manufacturers of material selection and line handling, but also used in the car.

"We have a client in Wuhan who is in charge of medicine distribution in Hubei. During the outbreak, we provided technical support to him to prevent the system from becoming unstable due to a surge in orders,"Sun Yu, co-founder of Kuaokang intelligence, told CNFC.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Smart Warehouse Robot Works in the warehouse

But Sun said the warehouse was working well. The last kilometer of the open environment is indeed difficult. There are still many challenges in the normal operation of unmanned vehicles, mainly due to the complexity of the environment and the weather, legal risk uncertainty and other factors. In the transport sector, he is more optimistic about unmanned container trucks (unmanned container trucks) this product form, especially the trunk logistics of unmanned trucks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Hirataira" and "ann-ann" are delivering supplies at the hospital

The outbreak, so that "automatic guided vehicle (AGV) + " composite products have been more widely used.

The Guangdong General Hospital introduced twin robots, "Hirataira" and "an' an, " to deliver meals, medicine, clothing and medical waste in isolation wards and infection departments. Later, various kinds of disinfection robots, inspection robots, temperature measuring robots, etc. , all innovate on the basis of AGV, so as to meet the application of various scenarios.

Ai Algorithm shortens analysis time, helps research and development of new drugs, vaccines

SCENE: The lab

During the new crown pneumonia epidemic, Baidu, Alibaba, Shang Tang and other enterprises took the approach of opening up their core algorithms and computing power, and worked together with medical research institutions to combat the epidemic, it is mainly used for viral gene sequencing, new drug and vaccine development, protein screening and so on.

These are achieved in the laboratory by computer comparison and calculation, using artificial intelligence algorithms, the original hours of suspected cases of genetic analysis can be reduced to half an hour, and can accurately detect the virus mutation, to buy US some quality time.

According to Wei Ming Xiong, a partner at Huachuang capital, a drug typically takes $1 billion or 10 years to develop, and with the help of Ai, that time could be shortened considerably. On the other hand, AI is not a hot market, and it takes time to start a business in this area.

He said that in foreign countries, companies like Schrödinger, which has been in business for 30 years, will have a revenue of only $60 million in 2018, compared with black diamond, which went public less than six years after it was founded, but so far only two preclinical drugs have been made. So the industry is still waiting to see if AI can deliver the desired results.

Image / visual China

Using artificial intelligence to help develop new drugs is not a new topic. As early as October 1981, the cover of Fortune Magazine reported that Merck & Co. was using computers to help make new drug discovery more efficient. But none of the drugs developed by AI have come to market yet.

"drug development is a very long process and the costs are huge. In this process, the current role of AI is to accelerate the screening of compounds, but after clinical, the role is relatively limited,"said Li Ming, CAS CAPITAL Executive Director.

For pharmaceutical companies, the ultimate value of the company depends on the pipeline of new drugs, pre-clinical conditions and target selection and so on. Therefore, from the entrepreneurial point of view, Xiong Weiming should be from the pharmaceutical sector upstream and downstream and peripheral cut-in, will have a comparative advantage. If the startup has both AI capabilities and an understanding of the pharmaceutical industry, there's a huge opportunity.

Conclusion

Some scenes will settle down after the outbreak

But it does not determine the future of AI enterprises

Will the epidemic eventually pass, and will the need for Ai Fade in all areas?

"Ai Penetration is phased and most startups are now focused on image and voice semantics, where customers are concentrated in security and finance, where demand is rigid and the ability to pay is strong. Now Ai is also beginning to penetrate into the industrial sector, but the industry is waiting to see where AI enterprises should go next,"said Li Ming, executive director of CAS capital.

Overall, the AI companies are responding quickly to the outbreak, Li Ming said, but with many products in the upstream supply chain now priced out of the market, and the pressure to resume work, AI companies will be under a lot of pressure.

After the epidemic has passed, some scenes will eventually settle down. For example, the Beijing Capital International Airport thermometer was used during SARS, the Beijing subway security checks were used during the Olympics, and the outbreak has also accumulated some scene usage habits.

"But in retrospect, the new features and products in these scenarios were not the most critical thing that determined the development of an AI enterprise. Epidemic of all industries will be a big shuffle, backward model, single products, financial situation is not pass the enterprise will be eliminated. This epidemic is a catalyst, but enterprises can not develop with catalyst alone. Instead, the big waves will test small and medium-sized AI enterprises,"Li Ming said.
